==English==
===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/θɔː/}}

===Verb===
'''to thaw''' ([[thaws]], [[thawed]], [[thawing]])

====Intransitive====
# To [[melt]], [[dissolve]], or become [[fluid]]; to [[soft]]en; — said of that which is [[frozen]]; as, the [[ice]] thaws.
# To become so [[warm]] as to [[melt]] [[ice]] and [[snow]]; — said in [[reference]] to the [[weather]], and used impersonally.
# Fig.: To [[grow]] [[gentle]] or [[genial]].

====Transitive ====
To cause (frozen things, as earth, snow, ice) to melt, soften, or dissolve.

=====Translations=====
*Romanian: [[decongelare]]


===Noun===
'''thaw'''

# The melting of ice, snow, or other congealed matter; the resolution of ice, or the like, into the state of a fluid; liquefaction by heat of anything congealed by frost; also, a warmth of weather sufficient to melt that which is congealed. —[[w:Dryden]].

